UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 647/GA
1 cabinet's website.
2 (b) The monthly report shall be a summary of the eligible project applications and
3 shall include but not be limited to the following:
4 1. A list of all eligible grant applications received;
5 2. The identity of applicants who were not selected for the obligation of
6 funds;
7 3. Trends found in feedback given to applicants who were not selected for
8 the obligation of funds; and
9 4. For each submitted eligible grant application:
10 a. The eligible use of funds and project for which funds are
11 requested;
12 b. The date of submission;
13 c. A description of the federal grant funds applied for by the
14 applicant;
15 d. A description of the title, subject matter, preliminary evaluation,
16 and scoring tally of the eligible grant application;
17 e. The date of the cabinet's preliminary evaluation;
18 f. The amount requested, and the amount approved or denied; and
19 g. The date of the cabinet's final decision on obligation of the match
20 funds, the date of the federal grant approval or denial, and whether
21 the eligible project was approved or denied.
22 (2) By November 1, 2024, and annually thereafter until November 1, 2028[2026], the
23 cabinet shall prepare an annual report of the GRANT Program to be submitted to
24 the Governor and the Interim Joint Committee on Appropriations and Revenue and
25 made available on the cabinet's website. The annual report shall include but not be
26 limited to the following:
27 (a) A summary of the monthly reports and the eligible grant applications received
Page 11 of 12
HB064710.100 - 1472 - XXXX 3/12/2026 2:41 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 647/GA
1 and relevant statistics relating to actions taken by the cabinet and grants
2 awarded, including the applicant, award amount, and the purpose of the
3 funding;
4 (b) The current balance of the GRANT Program fund;
5 (c) Recommendations regarding appropriations to the GRANT Program fund for
6 the upcoming fiscal year; and
7 (d) Recommendations for legislation or policy actions needed to facilitate greater
8 receipt of grant funding to eligible grant applicants.
9 Section 6. Whereas the GRANT program is available for a limited time period
10 and administrative efficiency requires that funding be allocated immediately, an
11 emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by
12 the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
